### Resume Entity Extraction – Testing Summary Report

The developed pipeline was tested on multiple types of input sources to ensure flexibility and robustness.

### 1. Input Types Tested

• Text-based PDF Resume
• Scanned PDF Resume (OCR-based extraction)
• DOCX Resume
• Direct Text Input
• LinkedIn Profile URL (public profiles)

---

### 2. Observations

• Text-based PDFs were processed accurately using PyMuPDF
• Scanned PDFs were successfully handled using OCR (Tesseract)
• DOCX parsing worked correctly with structured text extraction
• Direct text input produced the most accurate results
• LinkedIn extraction worked partially due to platform restrictions

---

### 3. Challenges Faced

• Noise in skill extraction due to absence of domain-specific filtering
• LinkedIn scraping limitations (authentication & rate limits)
• OCR accuracy depends on image quality

---

### 4. Conclusion

The pipeline successfully supports multiple input formats and produces structured JSON output.
A hybrid approach using NLP + rule-based extraction was used to ensure flexibility without hardcoding domain-specific skills.

---

### 5. Future Improvements

• Improve skill extraction using better NLP filtering
• Use advanced pretrained NER models for higher accuracy
• Integrate official APIs for LinkedIn data (if available)
